  "voiceover": "Aren't all religions basically the same? It sounds humble — all paths up the same mountain. But ask what they actually claim. Is God personal, or impersonal? One, many, or none at all? Did Jesus rise from the dead, or not? Is he God, a prophet, or a myth? These aren't small differences of flavor; they're flat contradictions at the core. And opposite claims can't both be true. That's not arrogance — it's arithmetic. The 'same mountain' picture actually smuggles in a huge claim: that you can stand above every religion and see what none of them can. To respect a faith is to let it mean what it actually says. So here's the honest option: they could all be wrong, but they can't all be right — which makes it worth finding out which one is.",
